# Monorepo sharing

Always extract shared configuration into `packages/` instead of duplicating it across apps.

- **Tooling** (`@fuel-carrier/web-config`): Vite, ESLint, TypeScript bases, Tailwind/DaisyUI CSS
- **Runtime** (`@fuel-carrier/web-ui`): React Query, TanStack Router helpers, shared providers
- **Types** (`@fuel-carrier/shared-types`): shared TypeScript types

Keep per-app only what truly differs: routes, env, branding, auth, and app-specific pages.

When adding new cross-app setup (Tailwind, Router, Query, ESLint, etc.), add it to the shared package first, then wire thin app-level entry files.
